rComments: The reason why this class is difficult is mainly due to the fact that Professor Galko usually teaches this class but things were different this semester. Professor D'Amours is one of the best professors in the Electrical Engineering Department with material straight to the point. You won't regret taking this class with , must have professor.
One of the best professors I had in uni.
He's one of the few profs that havent made this semester absolutely terrible.

If you looked up the definition of a "great professor" in a dictionary, Claude checks off all the boxes. I honestly have no interest in engineering, yet I'm still inclined to listen to him, which is awesome considering we have professors like Wail, Galko and Loyka in the department. Guy makes me want to learn French to take his classes. Tres bon!
Best prof in my whole degree. Lectures so good it makes me put my phone down and pay attention. Good sense of humor and actually cares about his students, very refreshing!!

no clue of how to teach. gives students marks to secure his own agenda/promotions regardless of the learning objectives. a vivid demonstration of why our educational system is not succeeding in developing quality engineers

Amazing prof. This class has a real chance of being a doozy, and many people skipped it, but Claude made the lectures really fun and engaging. I have learned a lot just by his stories and the guest speakers that might not appear on the exams but were worthwhile lessons. He takes a long time to grade things so expect to wait a long time for grades.

I couldn't imagine a better person to take Professional Practice with than Dr. D'Amours (the head of the EECS department). His real-life experience and anecdotes added tremendous value to the class, and made lectures worth attending. He is an engaging speaker who genuinely cares about his students. I recommend Dr. D'Amours without hesitation.
Excellent prof! Il explique et note bien en plus d'etre comprehensif!

Professor Claude is a fantastic lecturer and person. He has an awesome personality, importantly respecting the students, while having a high position in the faculty. This is hard to find since many professors are show offs with no student respect. Midterms and finals are not super easy but studying quizzes makes them much simpler. Recommend to all
The best professor at the University. Not just a good teacher but also has a great personality. One of the few Professors at the University who does not have a huge ego.
Top five profs of Uottawa.

This prof is a boss! Very chill and social. Slides are very clear. Makes the material interesting. Gives concrete examples about what he teaches. He's the Joseph Khoury of engineering. Overall it was a really fun and interesting class

I really appreciate that he is interested in electric guitar which is my favorite instrument. He likes to use some simple concept to convey the material of class, although I think some dynamic graph will be really useful instead of oral speaking in terms of some points. Overall, he is a good professor and he often keeps relationship with students.

Take his class, and you will fall in love with communications. He is awesome, knows his material and to top it off he is very friendly. He can at times speak too fast during lectures, slow him down. Also I would recommend schaum series of comms for extra questions as his assignments sometimes are not enough. He WANTS to teach you independent study.
Perfect. Awesome. Fun.
